      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an aging lab, look for a moderate protein to fat ratio, somewhere around 30-35% protein minimum. Too high in protein can sometimes strain older kidneys, while too little isn't ideal for maintaining lean muscle mass. Check the ingredient list to see if high-quality, bioavailable protein sources are featured early on for the best results. This balance should help support his muscle while managing weight gain.",
